-----------------------------------------------
OPTi 495XLC Write-Back Chipset
-----------------------------------------------


Filename   Port      Description  495XLC  386,486,Cyrix
--------   -------   ---------------------------------------------------------
V084B4B0   OPTI4B0   495XLC 386,486,Cyrix
V084B4B1   OPTI4B1   with  82C711 multi-IO
V084B4B2   OPTI4B2   with  PC87310 Super-IO
V084B4B3   OPTI4B3   with  PC87311 Super-IO
V084B4B5   OPTI4B5   with  8042 Turbo-Polling

Note - Vers 4B0-4B5  fully support Cyrix 486DLC in 386 socket as a
       "retrofit" without any special hardware considerations for it.
       (To maintain cache coherence, Cyrix CCR0 "BARB" is set, &tc).


V084B4B6   OPTI4B6   (Cx) 495XLC 386,486,Cyrix
V084B4B7   OPTI4B7   (Cx) with  82C711 multi-IO
V084B4B8   OPTI4B8   (Cx) with  PC87310 Super-IO
V084B4B9   OPTI4B9   (Cx) with  PC87311 Super-IO

V084B4BA   OPTI4BA   (Cx) with  OPTI-611 VL-IDE Controller
V084B4BB   OPTI4BB   (Cx) with  8042 Turbo-Polling
V084B4BG   OPTI4BG   (Cx) with  Green-PC Energy Mgmt  

Note - (Cx) - Vers 4B6-4BG  require specific "design-in" considerations for
       Cyrix 486DLC.  These pins must be connected: #FLUSH, #A20M.

       These versions give best Cyrix performance (compared with "retrofit"
       versions), but will MALFUNCTION unless the board is designed for it.


